cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem related to scheduling and resource allocation, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of LP-rounding algorithms and reductions to well-structured instances of generalized assignment points towards cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The focus on approximation algorithms and polynomial-time complexity suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the use of guessing tricks and parametric pruning suggests cs.IT (Information Theory).
